articles.author: Hilary Whiteman
articles.title: Australians vote No in referendum that promised change for First Nations people but couldn’t deliver - CNN
articles.description: With a two-letter word, Australians struck down the first attempt at constitutional change in 24 years, a move experts say will inflict lasting damage on First Nations people and suspend any hopes of modernizing the nation’s founding document.
